          <title>8. Did you know?</title>
          <para id="id1164571884331">Karl Friedrich Gauss (1777 - 1855) was 9 years old when his educator asked him to add all the numbers from 1 to 100. He did this in record time and the method he used is now known as the "Gauss method".</para>
